SAGE Automation is Australia's leading independent industrial automation and
control systems integrator. A recognised leader in the design, delivery and
support of industrial and electrical control solutions, SAGE Automation brings
the best thinking to clients across transport, manufacturing, resources,
Defence, utilities and infrastructure sectors.  
  
We currently seeking expression of interest from talented and enthusiastic
Graduate Engineers to join our Brisbane team. Graduate Engineers at SAGE are
able to combine professional and technical learning, on-the job learning
alongside ongoing mentoring whilst working on real-world, innovative projects.
There will be opportunity to work on industrial automation projects from kick-
off to hand over, including design documentation, PLC RTU and SCADA
programming, factory acceptance testing, on-site commissioning and hand-over
documentation.  
  
To be successful in this position you will:

  * Be highly motivated, enthusiastic, proactive and resourceful with a great attitude. 
  * Have knowledge of PLC, SCADA and HMI systems (Desirable). 
  * Basic understanding of electrical circuit fundamentals. 
  * Be highly competent at report and technical writing. 
  * Provide assistance with technical delivery and execution of projects. 
  * Work within a team environment alongside other junior and senior Engineers. 
  * Provide project assistance and support to the Project Managers and Support Technicians. 
  * Assist Estimators with the development of proposals and tender responses. 
  * Ability to maintain confidentiality, accuracy and prioritise work to meet conflicting deadlines. 
  * Possess the confidence and ability to liaise with management and internal staff. 

  
Key requirements:

  * Be an undergraduate or recent graduate of Electrical or Mechatronic Engineering. 
  * Have high computer competency, particularly with MS Office. 
  * Possess excellent communication and interpersonal skills. 
  * Have a strong desire and interest to work within the automation industry. 
  * Australian drivers licence. 
  * Must have the right to work in Australia. 

  
Our offering:.

  * Great opportunity to develop your career in a dynamic environment. 
  * Wide range of industries and project sizes. 
  * Competitive remuneration. 
  * Professional and safe working environment. 
  * SAGE supports and promotes cultural diversity and equal opportunity within the workplace. 

  
To apply online, please click on the advert link and send your resume and
cover letter addressing the responsibilities and skills.  
  
